{"word":"ὑπήκους","slug":"ὑπήκους","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑπήκους</b></el> <el>(ὑπ-ήκους, ουν,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀκοή'><el>ἀκοή</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>giving ear, listening to</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>obedient, subject to</i> another, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; so, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> rei, <el>ναυσὶν ὑπ.</el> <i>liable to furnish</i> ships, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <el>ὑπήκοοι, οἱ</el>, <i>subjects</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἡ ὑπήκοος</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>χώρα</el>); <el>τὸ ὑπήκοον</el> = <el>οἱ ὑπ.</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}